GENERAL SETUP:


always start with SUDO SU first
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EmSrQCDsMv4
1. install ruby
2. install jekyl
3. install bundle
4. create repo in github
5 cmd - jekly new . --force (crates the site with all folders and styles)
6 update repo
7. test website: bundle exec jekyll serve --livereload (http://localhost:4000)
8.modify gem files
9.modify config file
10.bundle update
11.bundle install 
(if you get an error delete gem.lock)
12. cmd: bundle update github-pages
13. _config. - base url  & url fill in... (base remove https: only have /whater ) (for url have only https://kmitchell0300.github.io)


